Manchester United came from behind to beat Chelsea 2-1 in their Barclays Under 21 Premier League encounter at Leigh Sports Village stadium on Monday evening.

Dominic Solanke gave the visitors the lead from close range after 55 minutes, before Andreas Pereira's deflected free-kick got the hosts back on level terms.

And defender Tom Thorpe completed the turnaround United, heading home emphatically from close range with just six minutes left on the clock.  

