The pivotal moment in the match came when Rafael went on another marauding run forward, to be eventually hauled down on the edge of the Chelsea penalty area.

Andreas Pereira took the honour and his effort deflected cruelly off Jay Dasilva in the Chelsea wall and wrong footed Mitchell Beeney to level the match.

That was the catalyst for United as minutes later Pereira flashed in another long range free-kick, only for Beeney to pull off a fine reaction save.

