Finally, United were in the ascendancy and made the pressure count in a tense final ten minutes.

Pereira was once again involved, whipping in a teasing cross when United captain Tom Thorpe rose unmarked to head the hosts into the lead.

Despite the best efforts of Chelsea to find an equaliser, United held on to go joint top of the table alongside Chelsea and Southampton, who lost to Everton.

